Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
queryPinDensity(25.10)                                  queryPinDensity(25.10)

Name
       queryPinDensity - Outputs pin density for the design

Syntax
       queryPinDensity

       [-help]

       [-area <x1 y1 x2 y2>]

       Outputs  pin  density for the design. The argument type is box in units
       of microns.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each queryPinDensity parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man queryPinDensity

       -area  Species the box coordinates in microns.

              * <x1>: Specifies the area's lower left point on the x axis.

              * <y1>: Specifies the area's lower left point on the y axis.

              * <x2>: Specifies the area's upper right point on the x axis.

              * <y2>: Specifies the area's upper right point on the y axis.

Examples
       The  following  command  reports  the pin density for the specific area
       43.24 23.505 139.626 113.411:

       queryPinDensity -area 43.24 23.505 139.626 113.411

       calculate placement pin density in box (43.20, 16.00,  140.00,  120.00)
       Pin Density = 0.3223.

        = total # of pins 507 / total area 1573.

